    "description": "This fixes an issue with field detection that was exposed by the changes in [PR 746](https://bitbucket.org/yt_analysis/yt/pull-request/746/adding-niceties-for-field-detection).  Before we allowed fields added by `derived_field` that might raise errors to silently fail.  Now that we let the errors get raised, this caused field detection to break during the unit tests due to the `temperature` field not being defined for `fake_random_pf` and `beta_par` not being defined at module level in the `sunyaev_zeldovich` analysis module.\r\n\r\nThe root cause is the use of `@derived_field` in `sunyaev_zeldovich`, which triggers field detection errors if the `temperature` field is undefined.  This is often true. In particular, it is the default setting for `fake_random_pf`.\r\n\r\nRather than forcing all mock test datasets to include `temperature` (which is maybe a good idea, unfortunately it requires updating a lot of the tests), after chatting with Matt we decided to add the SZ fields using the field plugin API.\r\n\r\nLastly, I noticed that there was still some remnant code for the `projection_conversion` `DerivedField` parameter.  This has been made obsolete by the unit refactor and in fact wasn't hooked up to anything.  I've taken the opportunity here to remove the dead code and a few remnant references elsewhere in the code and docs.  Sorry that it clutters this PR - it was hard to logically separate out from the other changes to `DerivedField`.\r\n\r\nUpdate: using a better solution from Matt.",
